Description:
Veoneer is an automotive technology company, a world leader in active safety and restraint control systems, focused on delivering innovative, best-in-class products and solutions to our customers. Our purpose is to create trust in mobility. Veoneer is a Tier-1 hardware supplier and system integrator with products being part of more than 125 scheduled vehicle launches for 2022. Headquartered in Stockholm, Sweden, Veoneer has 6,100 employees in 11 countries. The Company is building on a heritage of close to 70 years of automotive safety development.
• What you’ll do?
• You will be part of a Research and Development team aiming to create new features for possible new products;
• You will analyze state of the art architectures and new solutions / algorithms, make proposals for new Proof Of Concept projects and contribute to their implementation;
• You will use your creativity to build up from scratch Proof Of Concept projects (data collection / annotation /cleaning / model creation ... training / optimization and demos);
• You will implement algorithms (vision / signal processing) to support the research work, optimize existing implementations for products core development;
• Use / optimize existing developments.
• What you’ll bring?
• Very good knowledge of machine learning for classification / clustering / optimization / regression problems;
• Very good knowledge of machine learning frameworks (Tensorflow / Keras);
• Very good python knowledge (virtual environments, numpy, Jupiter Lab, opencv, scikit-learn);
• Knowledge of C/C++, is a plus;
• Knowledge of embedded systems or ARM architectures / development, is a plus;
• Knowledge about devops (mlops skills will be highly appreciated)
• Understanding of Windows, Linux development and OOP;
• It will be considered an advantage some experience with full stack programming (web components integration

Company Description

Each one of us can contribute to a better future. You can do this on a daily basis on a labeling role.

AM (Autonomous Mobility) department develops products and systems based on intelligent Camera, Radar & Lidar sensors that are able to “see” and collect details from traffic in the surrounding area of the vehicles.

By joining our team, you will be part of the Labeling group for Deep Learning activities. Focus area covers Camera, Lidar and Radar technologies.

#AutonomousMobility

Job Description
• You will be labeling the data that comes from the different sensors based on the requirements agreed with the development.
• You will provide essential data to algorithms implemented using Deep Neural Network, and covering Object Detection, Lane detection, Semantic Segmentation, etc.
• You will be working together with the algorithm development team to find the best possible solution for data annotation.
• Highly flexible work.
• Technical university/technical... knowledge not needed.

A mentor will support you to stepwise take over own responsibility after an initial training phase which will familiarize you with our products, tools, processes and organization.

Qualifications
• Currently studying at University;
• Quality oriented, responsible, determined;
• English language;
• Highly motivated and willing to get involved in technical projects;
• Detail oriented mind;
• 8 hour availability

Would be a plus:
• Hungarian language,
• German language,
• Automotive knowledge,
• Experience in activities related to data labeling, data marking, data annotation, test and validation.

Additional Information

What we offer:
• Integration Program in a professional, young & dynamic team;
• A mentor for your learning period;
• Competitive Salaries & Benefits;
• Recommendation Bonuses for new team members;
• Flexible working hours for your studies.

Wellbeing:
• Health & Wellness (Private Health Insurance, Life Insurance, Sport activities etc.);
• Different discounts (glasses, tires, medical, shopping);
• In-house restaurant & coffee corners.

