Company Description

At Bosch, we shape the future by inventing high-quality technologies and services that spark enthusiasm and enrich people’s lives. Whether in areas of Automated Driving, Electric & Connected Mobility, IoT or Connectivity, our ideas make driving safer and more comfortable than ever before. This is only possible with the help of our colleagues from Bosch Engineering Center - with offices in Cluj and Bucharest - specialized in software, hardware & mechanics and reliability engineering. We work closely together with other international mobility development teams and with the local Bosch Cluj Plant in order to offer unique products and AIoT solutions to our clients from around the world.

So, are you ready to shape the future of the mobility together with us? Let us tell you more. Our promise to our associates is rock-solid: we grow together, we enjoy our work, and we inspire each other. Join in and feel the difference.

Job Description

Currently we are looking for a... self-motivated, enthusiastic Machine Learning DevOps Engineer to join our team and make it even stronger. Our team is responsible for enabling a wide variety of Bosch product teams to make use of progress in AI through centralized services that involve streaming data from connected services to building and deploying state-of-art AI solutions.

As a Machine Learning DevOps Engineer, you will be responsible for designing and implementing a cloud infrastructure for data-driven development, setting up CI/CD pipelines for projects by collaborating with Data Science, Software and Data Engineering teams. You will be part of a global team to make this happen!

In your role you will:
• design and implement a stable, highly available, performant, scalable and secure infrastructure;
• collaborate with data scientists and engineers to deploy new machine learning and deep learning solutions into complex and critical production systems;
• support Engineers with carrying out PoCs (Proof of Concepts) on cloud;
• work with Engineers to set up and maintain CI/CD pipelines for their projects on the cloud;
• create services for image searching, extraction, filtering, anonymization, compression, labelling and many others;
• work with cloud compliance groups within Bosch to ensure cloud subscriptions are compliant with Bosch’s cloud directives, policies and guidelines;
• ensure that cloud security concepts are rigorously implemented in accordance with Bosch security directives;

Technology Stack:
• Python
• Docker, Kubernetes
• Azure suite (e.g., Data bricks, Azure DevOps)
• Terraform
• Hadoop
• Jira, Git, GitHub, Agile

Qualifications
• Completed degree in Computer, Engineering or a comparable degree program;
• You have at least 3 years of experience in Cloud Infrastructure or DevOps roles;
• Hands-on experience in scripting languages, such as: Python, Shell script;
• You have hands on experience with IaaC tools like Terraform;
• Operating ETL (Extract Transform Load) pipelines;
• Experience with data centers, Hadoop HDFS, or other large filesystems;
• Knowledge about cloud security concepts;
• Having knowledge and experience in CI/CD Tools such as Git, GitHub, Bitbucket, Artifactory;
• Familiar with API protocols (e.g., REST API protocol);
• Personality and working practice: self-organized and goal-oriented, take responsibility and strong analytical thinking skills, team player, customer-focused working style;
• Fluent in English, both verbal and written;

Nice to have:
• Knowledge of C++/JavaScript programming languages;
• Machine learning on a basic level (TensorFlow, Keras, PyTorch);
• A public Cloud Certification, preferably Azure;
• Willingness to undertake business trips abroad for trainings and project work;
• German language;

